# ScottFree (Scott Adams) regression test.
#
# Game: baton.dat -- "The Golden Baton", #1 of Brian Howarth's Mysterious
# Adventures (1981). Text-only Scott Adams format database, freely
# distributable (the author permitted upload to the IF Archive). Source:
# https://ifarchive.org/if-archive/scott-adams/games/scottfree/mysterious.tar.gz
#
# Regression guard for the glk_window_close pair-window bug (window.zig):
# an arrange event makes ScottFree close and reopen its status/graphics
# windows. glk_window_close used to destroy a window without collapsing its
# parent pair, leaving a dangling child pointer that recalculateLayout() then
# wrote through -- corrupting the heap and trapping ("memory access out of
# bounds") on the NEXT command. This test arranges, then moves, and must not
# crash.

** game: baton.dat
** remformat: yes

* arrange-then-move
{status} I'm in a dense SPOOKY Forest
>{arrange} 900 480
{status} I'm in a dense SPOOKY Forest
> north
{status} I'm by a Stream
> south
{status} I'm in a dense SPOOKY Forest
